<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871015-0019 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:3Com Corp. Picks Bradley,Paisley for Executive Posts</HL><DD> 10/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> COMS WNEWS </IN><DATELINE> SANTA CLARA, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Jack A. Bradley, vice president and chief financial officer of Bridge Communications Inc., was named a senior vice president and general manager, international division, of 3Com Corp.    The maker of computer network products, which last month completed its merger with Bridge, also said that it named Christopher B. Paisley vice president and chief financial officer.    With Mr. Bradley's appointment, the company said its new international division will take on increasing importance. Currently, international business accounts for 30% of the combined companies' revenue, but that business is expected to grow at twice the rate of North American sales in the next two to three years, 3Com said. </TEXT></DOC>